/**
 * curl_tests.http contains sample HTTP requests for testing API endpoints.
 */

### Run the app
### Install REST Client plugin for VSCode to have a button "Send Request" above each of the command here. 
### Or you can also test it in terminal (with the running app in another terminal) using curl, like:
### curl -X GET http://localhost:5000/api/products

### Get all products
GET http://localhost:5000/api/products

### Get product by ID
GET http://localhost:5000/api/products/1

### Create a new product
POST http://localhost:5000/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Product",
  "description": "Test Description",
  "price": 123.45
}

### Update a product
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/products/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Product",
  "description": "Updated Description",
  "price": 150.00
}

### Delete a product
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/products/1

### Get all orders
GET http://localhost:5000/api/orders

### Get order by ID
GET http://localhost:5000/api/orders/1

### Create a new order
POST http://localhost:5000/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productIds": [1, 2],
  "totalPrice": 300.00
}

### Delete an order
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/orders/1

### Get Products
GET http://localhost:5000/api/product

### Post Product
POST http://localhost:5000/api/product
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Name": "Test Product",
  "Description": "Test Description",
  "Price": 123.45
}

### Get Orders
GET http://localhost:5000/api/order